    "kit": {
      "info": {
        "contact": {
          "email": "support@thecocktaildb.com"
        },
        "description": "Provides access to a free cocktail recipe API with various endpoints for searching cocktails, ingredients, and more. Supports JSON format. Test API key '1' can be used for development and educational purposes. Premium API subscription required for production use.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server (using test API key '1')",
            "url": "https://www.thecocktaildb.com/api/json/v1/1"
          }
        ],
        "termsOfService": "https://www.thecocktaildb.com/terms",
        "title": "Cocktail Recipe API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Search, filter, and look up cocktail recipes, ingredients, and drink images from TheCocktailDB",
        "homepage": "https://www.thecocktaildb.com/",
        "docs_url": "https://www.thecocktaildb.com/api.php",
        "license_short": "Free for development with test key `1`; production use requires a Premium API subscription.",
        "license_md": "- Free basic access using the development test key `1` (URL path `/api/json/v1/1`).\n- Production / commercial use requires a Premium API subscription via [TheCocktailDB](https://www.thecocktaildb.com/api.php).\n- Premium-only features include multi-ingredient filtering, popular/recent lookups, image API methods, and full database access beyond the 100-item limit.\n- Attribution to TheCocktailDB is appreciated; check the site's terms for the current policy before redistributing data or images.",
        "about_md": "[TheCocktailDB](https://www.thecocktaildb.com/) is a community-maintained, crowd-sourced database of cocktail recipes, ingredients, and drink imagery. It is run by the same UK-based team behind TheMealDB and exposes a simple JSON HTTP API at `https://www.thecocktaildb.com/api/json/v1/{key}`.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- Search drinks by name, by first letter, or search ingredients by name (`search.php`).\n- Look up full cocktail details by drink ID or ingredient details by ingredient ID (`lookup.php`).\n- Fetch a random cocktail (`random.php`).\n- Filter drinks by ingredient, alcoholic / non-alcoholic status, category, or glass type (`filter.php`).\n- List the available categories, glasses, ingredients, and alcoholic filter values (`list.php`).\n- Cocktail and ingredient images in multiple sizes (200/350/500 px for drinks; 100/350/700 px for ingredients).\n\nOperational notes: the API is JSON over HTTPS with CORS enabled, so it can be called directly from browsers. The development key `1` is rate-limited and capped at roughly 100 results per query; multi-ingredient filtering, popular / latest endpoints, and the image API methods are gated behind the Premium tier.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "filter": "Filter drink lists by a single attribute such as ingredient, alcoholic status, category, or glass via `filter.php` (e.g. `filter.php?i=Gin`, `filter.php?a=Alcoholic`, `filter.php?c=Cocktail`, `filter.php?g=Cocktail_glass`).",
          "list": "Enumerate the controlled vocabularies used by the filter endpoints — categories, glasses, ingredients, and alcoholic/non-alcoholic values — via `list.php` (e.g. `list.php?c=list`).",
          "lookup": "Retrieve a full record by ID — a cocktail by drink ID or an ingredient by ingredient ID — via `lookup.php` (e.g. `lookup.php?i=11007`, `lookup.php?iid=552`).",
          "random": "Return a single randomly chosen cocktail with its full recipe via `random.php`.",
          "search": "Search cocktails by name or first letter, or search ingredients by name via `search.php` (e.g. `search.php?s=margarita`, `search.php?f=a`, `search.php?i=vodka`)."
        },
        "auth": false
      },
